In case you get stuck:

1. Make sure to add the .csv files that were in the project description
    * the code expects a file called "test.csv" and "train.csv" to be loacated in data\stage_2_data

2. Make sure your virtual envirionment is set up with the right packages 
    * the main ones are scikit-learn, numpy, and torch

3. The file you want to run is in ..\script\stage_2_script\script_mlp.py
    * I set it up to where both the system path and the working directory should both start in the /ECS170_Spring_2026_Source_Code_Template folder. You should be able to run the file either through the IDE or manually through the terminal

    ** If running using terminal **
    You will have to manually close out of the plots from matplotlib for the code to continue running
    


--

* install matplotlib for the plot to show
* had path issues due to local code location, used PYTHONPATH= .../ecs170-group-project/ECS170_Spring_2026_Source_Code_Template python script/stage_2_script/script_mlp.py
